
GIT DIFF !!

We can use the git diff command to view changes between committs, branches, files, working directory and many more. 
we use it side by side with git status and git log, to get a better picture of a repo and how it has changed over time.
It will lists all the changes in the working directory that are not staged for the next commit. 

> Commands -
-- Lists changes in the working directory
   [ git diff] 
-- Lists all changes in the working directory since the last commit
   [ git diff HEAD] 
-- Viewing staged changes ( It will list the changes between the staging area and our last commit)
   [ git dff --staged] 
   [ git diff --cached]  
